Abstract = {Renewable Energy (RE) is rapidly gaining relevance as a key technology
   to quench growing energy demand on the African continent. Many African
   states have introduced RE legislation, but the design of RE policy
   instruments, as well as their application and efficiency vary
   considerably across African economies. This article presents an analysis
