Abstract = {The concept of a `just transition' to a low-carbon economy is firmly
   embedded in mainstream global discourses about mitigating climate
   change. Drawing on Karl Polanyi's political economy elaborated in The
   Great Transformation, we interrogate the idea of a just transition and
   place it within its historical context. We address a major contradiction
   at the core of global energy transition debates: the rapid shift to
   low-carbon energy-systems will require increased extraction of minerals
