Volume = {68},
Month = {OCT},
Abstract = {The energy landscape is changing dramatically. Communities are being
   impacted in different ways. Positive impacts include reductions in air
   pollution and new tax revenues from renewables. Negative impacts include
   lost jobs and foregone tax revenues after closure of large fossil fuels
   generation facilities and coal mines. The contours of this transition
   have been further altered by recent events such as the global oil market
   crash and the COVID-19 pandemic. While economic and social issues can be
   addressed through thoughtful policy design, the pace of change, and the
   extent to which communities have a say in what comes next, matter.
   Though the technical issues of transitions are well-researched, the
