   delays, proceeding too slowly; and its extension of reliable and
   affordable electricity has been hampered by both irregularities of
   coal-generated supply, as well as austerity-driven delivery policies.
   This paper argues however that the concurrence of two, previously
   sequential historical events - fiscal crisis and intra-regime schism -
